In this paper, for simplicity, we consider the case where $F$ is a color-triplet and SU(2) singlet vector-like fermion
field, $T$, with charge $Q_F = +2/3$. We assume that the vector-like fermion mixes with the SM top-quark only.
This model was chosen such that in the heavy particle limit it
introduces all the (CP-even) dimension-6 operators that affect Higgs physics and are not severely constrained by electroweak precision physics. Such a model has also been considered in \cite{Xiao:2014kba} in the context of stabilizing the electroweak vacuum in the presence of new vector-like fermion representations. We intend on returning to the other possibilities, some of which have been garnering interest recently in the context of the 750~GeV diphoton excess, in future publications.

