Both the ratios $v_H/v_S$ and $m_t/m_T$ are already driven towards the decoupling limit by current measurements of the Higgs properties (as well as the $S$ and $T$ parameters), with 68\% confidence intervals restricting $v_H/v_S\leq 0.85$ and $m_t/m_T\leq 0.42$.  



